  "summary": "Anthony meets with Mr. Azerbaijan (also referred to as Isakov or Isaacstan) to negotiate a deal regarding Hesslegrave and oil rights in Eisakstan. Anthony proposes finding a pro-English heir to the throne to secure these rights, suggesting a cash deal under the same loan terms previously offered to the late Prince Michael. When Azerbaijan refuses Anthony's request to meet at the Chimney Villa that night due to a dinner engagement, Anthony reveals that the gun used to kill Prince Michael was found in Azerbaijan's suitcase. Although Azerbaijan claims this is a lie, Anthony whispers a suggestion in his ear that leaves him stunned.\n\nLater, at nine o'clock, a gathering takes place in the council chamber of the Chimney Villa. The Earl of Carrington, who expresses weariness regarding the group, joins Bunder, the Earl of Chatham, George Romax, Everleigh, Bill, and Bandel. The group discusses the disappearances of Mr. Fischer and Virginia, noting that Virginia left a note. They observe a mix of detectives and officials and note the absence of Victor King (Kidd), whom they suspect is orchestrating the meeting from afar. Anthony arrives and announces that secrets will be revealed. He explains that a previously undecipherable cipher can be solved using the memoirs of the late Count Stapleton. By connecting the Count's rose emblem to a \"flower\" theme and identifying rows of items, Anthony concludes that the cipher refers to the Earl of Carrington's library. He asserts that the hidden jewels are concealed behind or within a fake book titled \"The Earl of Richmond.\"",
